-- Darty Denies Plan to Sell Turkish Stores; Aims to Expand
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-08-10T14:50:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-10/darty-denies-plan-to-sell-turkish-stores-aims-to-expand.html
Darty Plc (DRTY) , the London-based consumer
electronics retailer, denied a report in the Turkish media that
it plans to sell stores in the country.  Darty will grow in  Turkey  by opening five stores a year, it
said in an e-mailed statement today.  Teknosa Ic & Dis Ticaret AS, Turkey’s biggest electronics
retailer that hired  HSBC Holding Plc (HSBA)  for acquisitions, may
target Darty’s stores in Turkey,  Milliyet newspaper  said today.  Darty has 28 stores in Turkey, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
